@DATABASE Test.guide

@NODE Main "Script DataType - Test File 1"

@{B}Cloanto Script DataType@{UB} ą

This document is designed to be displayed with MultiView or AmigaGuide
compatible viewers.

A double-click on the "Test_1" icon executes a script which searches for
either MultiView or AmigaGuide in a standard location on the system, and
then uses that software to display this document. If this fails, it is
most likely that neither program could be found. Normally, these viewers
are located in "SYS:Utilities".

If you double-clicked on "Test_1" and you are now reading this text with
either MultiView or AmigaGuide, it means that these viewers were found and
can be used to execute "Test_2".

As an additional test, you can "drag and drop" either "Test_1" or "Test_2"
onto a viewer which uses Amiga DataTypes. This will test whether the Script
DataType is installed and running.

The Script DataType enables "drag and drop" of AmigaDOS scripts such as
these test files. Without the Script DataType, it is most likely that the
files will be displayed as a series of AmigaDOS commands. When the Script
DataType is installed, the test files are executed, rather than displayed.

Your feedback on this software is very appreciated.


